The funeral service for industrialist and Capital Group Limited chairman Chris Kirubi is currently ongoing at the Faith Evangelistic Ministry (FEM) church in Karen. The service commenced at 11 am and guests are expected to be seated by 10:30am. Kirubi's burial is set for Saturday at his farm in Thika. The burial ceremony will begin at 11am. Kirubi, 80, died on Monday June 14, 2021 at his home after a long battle with cancer.